            <title>[HBASE-11717] Remove unused config &apos;hbase.offheapcache.percentage&apos; from hbase-default.xml and book</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11717</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;hbase.offheapcache.percentage is unused now.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;property&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;hbase.offheapcache.percentage&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;0&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;description&amp;gt;The percentage of the off heap space (-XX:MaxDirectMemorySize) to be
     allocated towards the experimental off heap &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;SlabCache&quot;&lt;/span&gt; (This is different to
     the BucketCache -- see the &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; javadoc &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; org.apache.hadoop.hbase.io.hfile
     &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; more on your options). If you desire the cache to be disabled, simply set &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;
      value to 0.&amp;lt;/description&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
